name: Dunk Low 'Black White'
description: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Black White’ also known as 'Panda' treats the retro model to an essential two-tone color scheme that accentuates the sneaker’s clean lines.

name: Dunk Low 'Concord'
description: The Nike Dunk Low 'Concord' is built with smooth leather construction, featuring a crisp white base with bluish purple overlays and a color-matched Swoosh.

name: Dunk Low 'Gym Red'
description: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Gym Red’ showcases a familiar two-tone design that recalls the original ‘Be True to Your School’ series from 1985.

name: Dunk Low Pro SB 'Freddy Krueger'
description: With the Dunk Low Pro SB ‘Freddy Krueger,’ Nike pays tribute to the villain that haunts the Nightmare on Elm Street film franchise.

name: Concepts x Dunk Low SB 'Purple Lobster'
description: Concepts and Nike SB are back at it again, with a new iteration of the 'Lobster' inspiration.

name: Ben & Jerry's x Dunk Low SB 'Chunky Dunky'
description: Made in collaboration with Ben & Jerry’s, the Nike Dunk Low SB ‘Chunky Dunky’ replicates the packaging used for the ice cream brand’s Chunky Monkey flavor.

name: Off-White x Air Force 1 Low '07 'MoMA'
description: Designed by Virgil Abloh, the Off-White x Air Force 1 Low '07 'MoMA' was unveiled at Art Basel Miami Beach 2016.

name: Air Force 1 '07 'Triple White'
description: he Nike Air Force 1 ‘07 ‘Triple White’ gives the classic silhouette a blank-slate makeover, one that accentuates the shoe’s classic lines.

name: Supreme x Air Force 1 Low 'Box Logo - Baroque Brown'
description: The Supreme x Nike Air Force 1 Low ‘Box Logo’ steps out in ‘Baroque Brown.’

name: Zoom Kobe 6 Protro 'Grinch' 2020
description: The Nike Zoom Kobe 6 Protro ‘Grinch’ 2020 brings back a beloved colorway initially released in 2010 as part of the Nike Basketball Christmas Day Collection.

name: Air Max 1 'Monarch'
description: In collaboration with Patta, the Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Monarch (with Bracelet) features a grey mesh upper with white overlays with Monarch Swooshes and a wave-shaped mudguard.

name: Air Foamposite One 'Metallic Red' 2023
description: The 2023 reissue of the Nike Air Foamposite One ‘Metallic Red’ brings back a vibrant colorway of the retro hoops shoe originally released in 2012.
